## Epic → Sprint → Story Workflow

### Epic Creation

**Purpose:** Define high-level business initiative

**Process:**
```
1. Create epic document: ai_docs/Epics/[epic-id].epic.md
2. Define business goals and success metrics
3. Estimate overall scope (story points)
4. Identify target sprints
5. Break down into high-level features
```

**Epic Template:**
```markdown
---
id: EPIC-001
title: [Epic Title]
status: Planning
start_date: 2025-11-01
target_date: 2025-12-15
total_points: 50
created: 2025-10-30
---

# Epic: [Title]

## Business Goal
[What business problem does this solve?]

## Success Metrics
- [Metric 1: e.g., Reduce checkout time by 30%]
- [Metric 2: e.g., Increase conversion rate by 15%]
- [Metric 3: e.g., Support 10,000 concurrent users]

## Scope
[High-level features included in this epic]

### Features
1. Feature 1
2. Feature 2
3. Feature 3

## Target Sprints
- Sprint 1: Features 1-2
- Sprint 2: Features 3-4
- Sprint 3: Polish & performance

## Dependencies
- [External dependencies or prerequisites]

## Stakeholders
- Product Owner: [Name]
- Tech Lead: [Name]
- Team: [Team name]
```

### Sprint Planning

**Purpose:** Plan 2-week iteration with specific stories

**Process:**
```
1. Create sprint document: ai_docs/Sprints/[sprint-id].sprint.md
2. Select stories from epic backlog
3. Estimate team capacity (velocity)
4. Prioritize stories based on business value
5. Assign story points to each story
6. Define sprint goals
```

**Sprint Template:**
```markdown
---
id: SPRINT-001
epic: EPIC-001
start_date: 2025-11-01
end_date: 2025-11-15
capacity: 20 points
status: Planning
---

# Sprint 1: [Sprint Name]

## Sprint Goal
[What will we achieve this sprint?]

## Stories

### High Priority (Must Have)
- [ ] STORY-001: User registration (5 points)
- [ ] STORY-002: User login (3 points)

### Medium Priority (Should Have)
- [ ] STORY-003: Password reset (3 points)

### Low Priority (Nice to Have)
- [ ] STORY-004: Social login (5 points)

## Total Points: 16 / 20 capacity

## Daily Standup Notes
[Track daily progress]

## Sprint Retrospective
[To be completed at end of sprint]
```

### Story Creation

**Purpose:** Define atomic unit of work with testable acceptance criteria

**Process:**
```
1. Use story template
2. Write user story (As a [role], I want [feature], so that [benefit])
3. Define testable acceptance criteria (Given/When/Then format)
4. Define technical specification (API contracts, data models)
5. Define non-functional requirements (performance, security)
6. Estimate story points
7. Set priority
8. Initialize status: Backlog
```

**Story Template:**
```markdown
---
id: STORY-001
title: User Registration
epic: EPIC-001
sprint: SPRINT-001
status: Backlog
points: 5
priority: High
assigned_to: Developer Name
created: 2025-10-30
---

# Story: User Registration

## Description
As a new user, I want to register an account with email and password, so that I can access the platform.

## Acceptance Criteria

1. [ ] **Valid Registration**
   - Given a user with valid email and password
   - When the user submits registration form
   - Then account is created and confirmation email sent

2. [ ] **Email Validation**
   - Given a user with invalid email format
   - When the user submits registration form
   - Then validation error is displayed

3. [ ] **Password Requirements**
   - Given a user with password < 8 characters
   - When the user submits registration form
   - Then password strength error is displayed

4. [ ] **Duplicate Email**
   - Given an email already registered
   - When the user attempts to register
   - Then error message indicates email already exists

## Technical Specification

### API Endpoints

**POST /api/auth/register**
- **Request:**
  ```json
  {
    "email": "user@example.com",
    "password": "SecurePass123!",
    "firstName": "John",
    "lastName": "Doe"
  }
  ```
- **Response (201 Created):**
  ```json
  {
    "userId": "uuid",
    "email": "user@example.com",
    "message": "Registration successful. Please check your email."
  }
  ```
- **Response (400 Bad Request):**
  ```json
  {
    "error": "ValidationError",
    "details": {
      "email": "Invalid email format",
      "password": "Password must be at least 8 characters"
    }
  }
  ```

### Data Models

**User Entity:**
```csharp
public class User
{
    public Guid Id { get; set; }
    public string Email { get; set; }
    public string PasswordHash { get; set; }
    public string FirstName { get; set; }
    public string LastName { get; set; }
    public DateTime CreatedAt { get; set; }
    public bool EmailVerified { get; set; }
}
```

### Business Rules
1. Email must be unique across all users
2. Password must be hashed using bcrypt (minimum 10 rounds)
3. Email verification required before full account access
4. Confirmation email expires after 24 hours

## Non-Functional Requirements

### Performance
- Registration endpoint must respond within 500ms (p95)
- Support 100 concurrent registrations

### Security
- Passwords must be hashed with bcrypt
- No plaintext passwords in logs or error messages
- Rate limiting: 5 registration attempts per IP per hour
- HTTPS required for all auth endpoints

### Scalability
- Database must support 1M user records
- Email queue must handle 1000 emails/minute

## Dependencies
- Email service (SendGrid/AWS SES) must be configured
- Database migrations for User table
- None (can be implemented independently)

## Workflow Status
- [ ] Architecture phase complete
- [ ] Development phase complete
- [ ] QA phase complete
- [ ] Released

## Notes
[Additional context, design decisions, or clarifications]
```

